cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with security vulnerabilities in fitness trackers and proposes a protocol for secure data storage and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the design process of fitness trackers, which involves balancing various constraints, indicating a possible fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of sensors and data collection in fitness trackers suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes a new protocol for data storage and communication, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
